# E-Portfolio Implementation Plan for Filip Kehl

## Goal
Create a unique, immersive 3D e-portfolio for Filip Kehl, a Junior System Developer. The design should feature a specific color palette of Blue and Black and utilize advanced 3D animations to showcase technical skills and creativity.

> [!NOTE]
> This plan focuses on a "Cyber/Abyssal" aesthetic using deep blacks and vibrant blues.

## Technical Stack
- **Framework**: [Next.js](https://nextjs.org) (App Router)
- **Styling**: [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com) (configured with custom Blue/Black theme)
- **3D Graphics**: [Three.js](https://threejs.org), [React Three Fiber](https://docs.pmnd.rs/react-three-fiber), [Drei](https://github.com/pmndrs/drei)
- **Animations**: [Framer Motion](https://www.framer.com/motion) (for UI transitions), [GSAP](https://greensock.com) (optional for complex timelines)
- **Deployment**: Vercel (recommended)

## Design Concept: "The Digital Abyss"
- **Background**: Deep black (#050505) with subtle, dynamic blue (#0070f3, #00BFFF) nebula or grid effects.
- **Typography**: Modern sans-serif (e.g., *Inter* or *Space Grotesk*) for readability, with monospaced accents for a "developer" feel.
- **Interaction**: Mouse-driven parallax and lighting effects.

